<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="547" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/1560: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-07T19:00:00-03:00">August 7, 1940—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 7—6:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>333. Embassy’s 305, July 19, 3 p.m. The Minister for Foreign Affairs has
                            just requested me by telephone to inform you that his Government would
                            welcome the visit to Argentina of the mission referred to in the
                            Department’s 139, July 6, 6 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tuck</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>